1.title: Princes All
1.plot: A continuation of the second season; the team faces the difficulty of meta-human trafficking and a new intergalactic threat.

2.title: Royal We
2.plot: Dick Grayson, Artemis Crock, Conner Kent and Jefferson Pierce go undercover in Markovia to stop the Bedlam Syndicate's meta-human trafficking cartel - before it claims another victim.

3.title: Eminent Threat
3.plot: Conner Kent and Prince Brion Markov are in the clutches of Count Vertigo, leaving Dick Grayson, Artemis Crock and an emotionally damaged Jefferson Pierce to save them and put an end to the Bedlam Syndicate.

4.title: Private Security
4.plot: While Jefferson, Connor and Artemis find homes for their Markovian strays, Dick assembles a new squad and hits the road - but may not survive the trip.

5.title: Away Mission
5.plot: A distant conflict sends the team on an away mission while the Happy Harbor gang decide what to do with Brion Markov and Halo.

6.title: Rescue Op
6.plot: Brion Markov is determined to rescue his missing sister - even if it means throwing down against the entire League of Shadows.

7.title: Evolution
7.plot: Aliens once again threaten the Earth, but with the Justice League split and scattered, only Earth's first and greatest hero can save us!

8.title: Triptych
8.plot: As Meta-Human trafficking spreads across the United States, three very different teams of heroes seek to put a stop to it!

9.title: Home Fires
9.plot: The Light hires an assassin to take out a member of the team, but who's the target?

10.title: Exceptional Human Beings
10.plot: With no news on his sister, Brion is growing more and more impatient, but Batman's on the case.

11.title: Another Freak
11.plot: Victor confronts his father about his football game. Halo and Forager go to high school.

12.title: Nightmare Monkeys
12.plot: Garfield Logan tests out a pair of Goode VR goggles. Then the goggles test him.

13.title: True Heroes
13.plot: Grayson's operatives attempt to stop an auction of enslaved Meta-teens.

1.title: Independence Day
1.plot: Three teenage sidekicks decide to investigate a fire at a genetics laboratory... and discover a plot to create a clone of Superman.

2.title: Fireworks
2.plot: Robin, Kid Flash, and Aqualad are captured and only Superboy, the telepathically controlled clone of Superman, can free them. As they struggle to reach the surface, they must do battle with the transformed scientist known as Blockbuster.

3.title: Welcome to Happy Harbor
3.plot: Batman has yet to assign the team a mission, and the team grows restless. A fire at a nearby power plant is the team's first mission or is it just a test?

4.title: Drop-Zone
4.plot: Batman sends the team on its first official mission - to observe and report on a Venom Factory. The team chooses its leader.

5.title: Schooled
5.plot: Young Justice is assigned transport duty. To deliver parts of an android that has duplicated the powers of several Justice Leaguers. The creator of the android wants him back.

6.title: Infiltrator
6.plot: Roy rescues a scientist from the League of Shadows. He asks Young Justice to protect her and neutralize the weapon that she was working on. Artemis joins the team.

7.title: Denial
7.plot: When the team investigates the disappearance of Kent Nelson (formerly Doctor Fate), the scientific-minded Wally West is forced to confront his disbelief in magic while battling Abra Kadabra and Klarion the Witch Boy for the ultra-powerful helmet of fate.

8.title: Downtime
8.plot: After a poor performance during a mission, Batman gives the team some time off. Aqualad considers going back to Atlantis.

9.title: Bereft
9.plot: The team awakens in the Biaylan desert with amnesia. Miss Martian tries to unite the team to restore their memories, and must find the cause of their amnesia.

10.title: Targets
10.plot: Red Arrow has to protect one villain from another in order to ensure that peace talks between two warring nations go well.

11.title: Terrors
11.plot: Batman assigns Superboy and Miss Martian to go undercover inside Belle Reve, a federal prison designed to house the world's worst super-villains.

12.title: Homefront
12.plot: When the cave is attacked, can Artemis and Robin - the two teens without super-powers - save the Team (or even themselves) from the unknown invaders?

13.title: Alpha Male
13.plot: When Batman sends the Team and new "den-mother" Captain Marvel to India to investigate bizarre reports of armed animals attacking human beings, can Aqualad pull his fractured Team together?

14.title: Revelation
14.plot: Batman assigns the Team to battle the Injustice League, when plant creatures they control begin a global assault.

15.title: Humanity
15.plot: The Team is on the hunt for Red Tornado, and their friend Zatanna wants to come along for the ride.

16.title: Failsafe
16.plot: When the Justice League is defeated during an alien invasion, the Team has to step up and fill their mentors shoes.

17.title: Disordered
17.plot: Superboy's "Sphere" goes through a surprising change, revealing a connection to the forever people of New Genesis.

18.title: Secrets
18.plot: It's Halloween. Artemis and Zatanna are in Manhattan for a girls' night out. There, they encounter the deadly Harm, who has a secret.

19.title: Misplaced
19.plot: When Earth's 5 most powerful sorcerers make all the adults on the planet disappear, it's up to the Team, Zatanna, and Billy Batson to stop them.

20.title: Coldhearted
20.plot: On his birthday, Kid Flash must deliver a transplant heart in a race against time, artificial extreme weather conditions and supervillain opposition.

21.title: Image
21.plot: A covert operation against Queen Bee in Qurac forces Miss Martian to finally face her greatest fears and her biggest secrets. But will she reveal those secrets to her friends - or allow what she's hiding to take down the entire team?

22.title: Agendas
22.plot: Superboy returns to Project Cadmus, where he learns the top-secret genetics lab may have created another Super-clone...

23.title: Insecurity
23.plot: Red Arrow's return undercuts Artemis' confidence, while the team's mission to track down Sportsmaster threatens to expose her darkest secrets.

24.title: Performance
24.plot: Robin, Artemis, Superboy, Miss Martian, and Red Arrow go undercover as the Daring Dangers to discover the link between Haly's circus and stolen weapon technology.

25.title: Usual Suspects
25.plot: The team gets a new member and a new mission - a mission that may finally expose all of the team's secrets ... and all of their lies!

26.title: Auld Acquaintance
26.plot: The team finally learns the identity of the traitor in their midst, forcing a battle against an enemy more dangerous than any they've ever faced before!

1.title: Happy New Year
1.plot: Five years after the Justice League were controlled by Vandal Savage, their time under his control comes back to haunt them. The Team has to take on alien invaders, starting with Lobo.

2.title: Earthlings
2.plot: The team of Miss Martian, Superboy, Beast Boy and Adam Strange are sent to the planet Rann.

3.title: Alienated
3.plot: The invading Kroloteans receive aid from an unexpected ally.

4.title: Salvage
4.plot: Superboy and Blue Beetle take on Intergang, while Nightwing tries to salvage the soul of a former comrade.

5.title: Beneath
5.plot: Blue Beetle searches for a missing friend, while the team of Miss Martian, Batgirl, Bumblebee and Wonder Girl return to Bialya.

6.title: Bloodlines
6.plot: A mysterious intruder appears inside Mount Justice claiming to be a time-traveling visitor from the future.

7.title: Depths
7.plot: Artemis returns to the team to protect an important satellite launch.

8.title: Satisfaction
8.plot: Green and Red Arrow try and stop the original Speedy from taking his revenge on Lex Luthor.

9.title: Darkest
9.plot: An old friend returns to Mount Justice and takes revenge to prove himself to his new masters.

10.title: Before the Dawn
10.plot: Aqualad meets the Light's partner and learns of their plans for Earth while Miss Martian's revenge backfires on her. Meanwhile, the team meets a new, seemingly unbeatable super villain.

11.title: Cornered
11.plot: The team is trapped inside the Hall of Justice for a cage match against a brutal alien gladiator!

12.title: True Colors
12.plot: When the Reach forms a devil's alliance with Lexcorp, Robin leads a squad undercover to investigate.

13.title: The Fix
13.plot: Black Manta seeks vengeance against Miss Martian.

14.title: The Runaways
14.plot: Nightwing tasks Blue Beetle with chasing down a group of potentially dangerous super-powered teenage runaways. But Blue Beetle is not the only one hunting them....

15.title: War
15.plot: A conqueror from another world becomes a wild card in an intergalactic game of supremacy - placing planet Earth square in the jackpot.

16.title: Complications
16.plot: Black Manta gives Miss Martian 24 hours to live, but that may be more time than Aqualad has, with Sportsmaster and Cheshire on the hunt for his head!

17.title: The Hunt
17.plot: A band of misfits is put to the test when Lex Luthor sends them behind enemy lines ... to rescue the team!

18.title: Intervention
18.plot: The team embarks on a desperate endeavor to free Blue Beetle!

19.title: Summit
19.plot: The Light calls a summit to decide the final fate of Aqualad, the team ... and the entire planet Earth!

20.title: Endgame
20.plot: When the earth is threatened by the Reach, the team must team up with Lex Luthor and fight the reach with out the Justice League.

imdb.plot outline: Within the Justice League, its members' teen sidekicks push for full membership, but it's only after they successfully investigate Cadmus in which find and free its secret young clone of Superman, Kon-El, is the League convinced. In response, the League organizes the teenagers into an apprentice team to both be trained and act on behalf of the League at their own pace. Now these teen superheroes, soon strengthened by more members, must battle the forces of evil in their own way, even as the mysterious cabal known only as The Light has a sinister agenda of their own.
imdb.title: Young Justice
plot: Teenage superheroes strive to prove themselves as members of the Justice League.::Kenneth Chisholm

synopsis:
In Young Justice, being a teenager means proving yourself over and overto peers, parents, teachers, mentors and, ultimately, to yourself. But what if youre not just a normal teenager? What if youre a teenage super hero? Are you ready to join the ranks of the great heroes and prove youre worthy of the Justice League? Thats exactly what the members of Young JusticeRobin, Aqualad, Kid Flash, Superboy, Miss Martian and Artemiswill find out, whether they have what it takes to be a proven hero. This all-new series is produced by Warner Bros. Animation and based upon characters from DC Comics.
Sam Register (Teen Titans, Ben 10, Batman: The Brave and the Bold) is the executive producer. Brandon Vietti (Batman: Under the Red Hood, Superman Doomsday, The Batman) and Greg Weisman (Gargoyles, The Spectacular Spider-Man, W.I.T.C.H.) are the producers.
